answer: In the lower mainland, immunization services are available at a variety of providers including all health units, most pharmacies, travel health clinics and some doctors offices. Hours of operation vary by location and many pharmacies (who immunize 5 years of age and older) are open 630pm or later. Some health units may offer clinics in the evening and/or weekends. Contact your local health unit. Use the health unit finder.
